01/02/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The majority of the Macedonian population supports the country's upcoming NATO membership, according to opinion polls conducted by the Centre for Ethnic and Security Issues at the Macedonian Institute for Sociological, Political and Judicial Research. 
According to the results published on Friday (30 January), 72.1 per cent of Macedonian citizens support Macedonia's NATO accession while only 13.3 are against it. 
The poll also shows that 53.3 per cent of Macedonian citizens support strategic partnership with the United States. 
(MIA - 30/01/04)
